gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 123, Nuggets 117
gameRecap.excerpt: Despite Nikola Jokics 36 points, 13 rebounds and 14 assists, the Nuggets fall to the Kings, 123-117. This is Jokics 8th triple-double on the season, and 113th of his career. DeAaron Fox recorded 26 points and a career-high 16 assists for the Kings, while Malik Monk added 26 points and four 3PM in the victory. Reggie Jackson tallied 20 points and eight assists for the Nuggets in the losing effort. The Kings improve to 11-7 on the season, while the Nuggets fall to 14-7.
